import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.groupby('group')['person'].count().plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Group')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count of Persons')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of persons across the groups?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').count()['person']
    plt.hist(group_sizes, bins=range(1, max(group_sizes)+2), align='left', rwidth=0.8)
    plt.xlabel('Group size')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the most common group size?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(group_sizes.mode()[0], color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Most common group size: {group_sizes.mode()[0]:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.AutoFormatter())
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.table(cellText=data.values, colLabels=data.columns, loc='center')
    plt.title('What are the names of the persons in each group?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
